#: ../../source/comply/custom-terms-of-service.rst:9
msgid ""
"Increase clarity on legal Mattermost expectations for internal employees "
"and guests with the ability to set custom Terms of Service (“ToS”) "
"agreements and re-acceptable periods."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/comply/custom-terms-of-service.rst:12
msgid "Configuring terms of service"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/comply/custom-terms-of-service.rst:14
msgid "To enable custom terms of service:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/comply/custom-terms-of-service.rst:16
msgid "Go to **System Console > Compliance > Custom Terms of Service**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/comply/custom-terms-of-service.rst:17
msgid "Set **Enable Custom Terms of Service** to **true**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/comply/custom-terms-of-service.rst:18
msgid ""
"Set **Custom Terms of Service Text** which contains your terms. Markdown "
"formatting is supported, including lists, headings, and bolding."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/comply/custom-terms-of-service.rst:19
msgid ""
"Set **Re-Acceptance Period** to configure the number of days before Terms"
" of Service acceptance expires, and when the terms must be re-accepted. "
"Set to 0 if you don't want your terms to expire."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/comply/custom-terms-of-service.rst:20
msgid "Select **Save**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/comply/custom-terms-of-service.rst:22
msgid ""
"Once saved, all users must accept the terms of service by clicking **I "
"Agree** next time they log in, or on the next page refresh. If they do "
"not accept, they will be logged out."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/comply/custom-terms-of-service.rst:26
msgid ""
"If you make an update to your Terms of Service, make sure to update your "
"terms of service link at **System Console > Site Configuration > "
"Customization > Terms of Service link**. This link is presented to all "
"users when they log in, and it's easily accessible to end users after "
"accepting the terms."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/comply/custom-terms-of-service.rst:29
msgid "Frequently asked questions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/comply/custom-terms-of-service.rst:32
msgid "What happens if I update my terms of service text?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/comply/custom-terms-of-service.rst:34
msgid ""
"There will be no impact to your end users. Users will simply be required "
"to accept the new terms on next login or page refresh."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/comply/custom-terms-of-service.rst:37
msgid "What happens if a user doesn't accept the terms of service?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/comply/custom-terms-of-service.rst:39
msgid "Users won't be able to log in if they don't accept the Terms of Service."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/comply/custom-terms-of-service.rst:42
msgid "How do I know if my users accepted the terms of service?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/comply/custom-terms-of-service.rst:44
msgid ""
"Each time a user agrees to the terms of service, the agreement is "
"recorded in the database:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/comply/custom-terms-of-service.rst:46
msgid ""
"A new field ``AcceptedServiceTermsId`` in the **Users** table indicates "
"the most recent terms of service the user has accepted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/comply/custom-terms-of-service.rst:47
msgid ""
"Each time a user accepts the terms, the action is recorded in the "
"**Audits** table, containing the username, timestamp of acceptance, and "
"other relevant information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/comply/custom-terms-of-service.rst:50
msgid "Why isn't this feature in Team Edition for GDPR compliance?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/comply/custom-terms-of-service.rst:52
msgid ""
"Terms of service is presented to users on login and account creation, and"
" available to users at all times in the link available by going to "
"**System Console > Site Configuration > Customization**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/comply/custom-terms-of-service.rst:54
msgid ""
"This feature is intended to meet compliance requirements for large "
"Enterprise companies."
msgstr ""

